  1→NOTE: This operation creates or replaces a
  2→{rbtr_governor}
  3→within a
  4→{rbtgi_depot}.
  5→If a
  6→{rbtr_governor}
  7→already exists, it is deleted and replaced with a fresh one.
  8→This enables credential rotation and recovery from compromised keys.
  9→
 10→The
 11→{rbtr_payor}
 12→resets the
 13→{rbtr_governor}
 14→{giam_service_account}
 15→for a specified
 16→{rbtgi_depot_project}:
 17→
 18→// ⟦axs_inputs axd_none⟧
 19→. *Validate Input Parameters*:
 20→.. {rbbc_store}
 21→`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` from {rbrr_depot_project_id}
 22→.. {rbbc_require}
 23→`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` matches pattern `rbw-*-[0-9]{12}`
 24→
 25→// ⟦axs_behavior⟧
 26→. *Authenticate as
 27→{rbtr_payor}*:
 28→.. Execute
 29→{rbtoe_payor_authenticate}
 30→
 31→. *Depot Project Validation*:
 32→.. {rbbc_call}
 33→link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] to verify
 34→`«INPUT_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
 35→exists and is ACTIVE
 36→.. {rbbc_require}
 37→`«INPUT_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
 38→!=
 39→{rbrp_payor_project_id}
 40→
 41→. *Find and Delete Existing
 42→{rbtr_governor}
 43→Service Accounts*:
 44→.. {rbbc_call}
 45→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/list[iam.serviceAccounts.list]
 46→for
 47→`«INPUT_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
 48→.. {rbbc_store}
 49→`«EXISTING_GOVERNORS»` as service accounts matching pattern `governor-*`
 50→.. For each service account in `«EXISTING_GOVERNORS»`:
 51→... {rbbc_call}
 52→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/delete[iam.serviceAccounts.delete]
 53→to remove the service account
 54→... {rbbc_require}
 55→deletion successful (HTTP 200) or already deleted (HTTP 404)
 56→.. {rbbc_show}
 57→count of deleted governor service accounts
 58→
 59→. *Generate Governor Timestamp*:
 60→.. {rbbc_store}
 61→`«TIMESTAMP»` as current time in YYYYMMDDHHmm format
 62→.. {rbbc_store}
 63→`«GOVERNOR_ACCOUNT_ID»` as `governor-«TIMESTAMP»`
 64→
 65→. *Create the
 66→{rbtr_governor}
 67→{giam_service_account}*:
 68→.. {rbbc_call}
 69→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create]
 70→to create service account in
 71→`«INPUT_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
 72→.. Set `accountId` to `«GOVERNOR_ACCOUNT_ID»`
 73→.. Use display name: `Governor for RB Depot`
 74→.. {rbbc_store}
 75→`«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»` from response `.email` field
 76→.. {rbbc_require}
 77→service account creation successful (HTTP 200)
 78→
 79→. *Verify
 80→{giam_service_account}
 81→Propagation*:
 82→.. {rbbc_call}
 83→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get]
 84→to query service account using
 85→`«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»`
 86→.. {rbbc_poll}
 87→with 3-5 second intervals for up to 30 seconds if service account not immediately available
 88→.. {rbbc_require}
 89→service account accessible before proceeding
 90→
 91→. *Grant
 92→{gcp_project_id}
 93→-level Permissions*:
 94→.. {rbbc_call}
 95→link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/setIamPolicy[projects.setIamPolicy]
 96→to update IAM policy on
 97→`«INPUT_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
 98→.. {rbbc_use}
 99→`«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»` as principal
100→.. Add role: `roles/owner` (excluding billing permissions maintained by
101→{rbtr_payor})
102→.. Set policy version: 3 for conditional binding support
103→.. {rbbc_require}
104→IAM policy update successful
105→
106→. *Generate
107→{rbtgi_rbra_file}*:
108→.. {rbbc_call}
109→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create]
110→to create service account key for
111→`«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»`
112→.. Set keyAlgorithm: `KEY_ALG_RSA_2048`, privateKeyType: `TYPE_GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_FILE`
113→.. {rbbc_store}
114→`«GOVERNOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` from response `.privateKeyData` field
115→.. {rbtoe_rbra_generate}
116→converts
117→`«GOVERNOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»`
118→to
119→`{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}`
120→.. NOTE: Script outputs copy command for RBRA file installation
121→.. {rbbc_warn}
122→if
123→{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}
124→already exists (will be overwritten)
125→.. {rbbc_require}
126→RBRA file creation successful
127→
128→// ⟦axs_outputs⟧
129→. *Display Result*:
130→.. {rbbc_show}
131→governor reset successful
132→.. {rbbc_show}
133→governor service account: `«GOVERNOR_SERVICE_ACCOUNT»`
134→.. {rbbc_show}
135→RBRA file path:
136→{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}
137→
138→// ⟦axs_completion⟧
139→Successful execution resets governor state.
