  1→The
  2→{at_operator}
  3→completes one-time depot initialization after
  4→{rbtgo_depot_create}
  5→has provisioned infrastructure.
  6→This procedure validates the
  7→{rbra_rubric_repo_url}
  8→for {rbtgr_rubric_repo} management and completes the GitHub OAuth authorization for the
  9→{rbtgi_source_connection}
 10→created by
 11→{rbtgo_depot_create}
 12→in PENDING state.
 13→
 14→This procedure is idempotent — safe to re-run.
 15→Steps already complete (URL already valid, connection already COMPLETE) are skipped.
 16→
 17→// ⟦axs_inputs axd_none⟧
 18→
 19→// ⟦axs_preconditions⟧
 20→
 21→* {rbtgi_depot}
 22→exists (completed
 23→{rbtgo_depot_create})
 24→* {rbtr_governor}
 25→created for this depot (completed
 26→{rbtgo_governor_reset})
 27→* {rbrr_gdc_connection_name} and {rbrr_gdc_region} configured in RBRR
 28→* {rbrr_governor_rbra_file} contains {rbra_rubric_repo_url}
 29→* Operator has browser access for GitHub OAuth authorization
 30→
 31→// ⟦axs_behavior⟧
 32→
 33→. *Authenticate as
 34→{rbtr_director}*:
 35→.. Execute
 36→{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
 37→
 38→. *Load Rubric Repo URL*:
 39→.. {rbbc_call}
 40→{rbtoe_rbra_load}
 41→for
 42→{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
 43→.. {rbbc_store}
 44→`«RUBRIC_REPO_URL»` from {rbra_rubric_repo_url}
 45→.. If `«RUBRIC_REPO_URL»` is empty:
 46→... {rbbc_show}
 47→"RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL is not set in Governor RBRA file"
 48→... {rbbc_show}
 49→guidance for creating a rubric repository: create a repo on a git host (GitHub as reference example), generate a fine-grained PAT with Contents read/write, construct the authenticated URL as `https://x-access-token:<PAT>@<host>/<org>/<repo>.git`, and add `RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL` to the Governor RBRA file
 50→... {rbbc_fatal}
 51→"Set RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL in Governor RBRA file and re-run"
 52→
 53→. *Validate Rubric Repo URL*:
 54→.. {rbbc_call}
 55→`git ls-remote «RUBRIC_REPO_URL» HEAD` to verify reachability and credential validity
 56→.. If `git ls-remote` fails:
 57→... {rbbc_fatal}
 58→"Rubric repo URL is unreachable or credentials are invalid — check RBRA_RUBRIC_REPO_URL and ensure PAT has Contents:write permission"
 59→.. {rbbc_show}
 60→"Rubric repo URL validated"
 61→
 62→. *Check Developer Connect Connection Status*:
 63→.. Construct connection path: `projects/{rbrr_depot_project_id}/locations/{rbrr_gdc_region}/connections/{rbrr_gdc_connection_name}`
 64→.. {rbbc_call}
 65→link:https://cloud.google.com/developer-connect/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.connections/get[developerconnect.connections.get] for `«CONNECTION_PATH»`
 66→.. {rbbc_require}
 67→HTTP 200 — connection exists
 68→.. {rbbc_store}
 69→`«CONNECTION_STAGE»` from `.installationState.stage`
 70→.. If `«CONNECTION_STAGE»` is `COMPLETE`:
 71→... {rbbc_show}
 72→"Developer Connect connection already active — skipping OAuth step"
 73→... Go to step 7
 74→
 75→. *Grant Operator Console Access for Developer Connect*:
 76→.. {rbbc_require}
 77→{rbrp_operator_email} is set
 78→.. {rbbc_call}
 79→link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/setIamPolicy[projects.setIamPolicy] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
 80→.. Add `{rbrp_operator_email}` with `roles/developerconnect.admin`
 81→.. {rbbc_show}
 82→"Granted operator Developer Connect admin on depot project"
 83→
 84→. *Guide GitHub OAuth Authorization*:
 85→.. {rbbc_store}
 86→`«ACTION_URI»` from `.installationState.actionUri` of the connection response
 87→.. {rbbc_require}
 88→`«ACTION_URI»` is present and non-empty
 89→.. {rbbc_show}
 90→"Developer Connect connection requires GitHub OAuth authorization"
 91→.. {rbbc_show}
 92→`«ACTION_URI»` for {at_operator} to open in browser
 93→.. Guide {at_operator} through the OAuth flow:
 94→... GCP Console shows "Request GitHub OAuth token" — click "I understand and continue"
 95→... GitHub shows "Install Google Cloud Developer Connect" — select the account/org hosting the {rbtgr_rubric_repo}
 96→... Repository access: select "Only select repositories" and pick the {rbtgr_rubric_repo}
 97→... Click "Install"
 98→... GitHub redirects back to GCP; OAuth token stored in Secret Manager
 99→.. Wait for {at_operator} confirmation
100→
101→. *Poll Connection Until Active*:
102→.. {rbbc_poll}
103→link:https://cloud.google.com/developer-connect/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.connections/get[developerconnect.connections.get] for `«CONNECTION_PATH»`
104→.. Extract `.installationState.stage` from each response
105→.. Poll at `RBGC_EVENTUAL_CONSISTENCY_SEC` intervals until stage reaches `COMPLETE` or `RBGC_MAX_CONSISTENCY_SEC` timeout
106→.. {rbbc_require}
107→`installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
108→.. {rbbc_fatal}
109→if timeout: "Developer Connect OAuth did not complete — re-open the authorization URI and try again"
110→
111→. *Final Validation*:
112→.. {rbbc_show}
113→"Running final validation..."
114→.. Verify {rbtgr_rubric_repo} URL: repeat `git ls-remote` call — {rbbc_require} successful exit
115→.. Verify Developer Connect: repeat connections.get call — {rbbc_require} `installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
116→.. {rbbc_show}
117→"Depot initialization complete"
118→
119→// ⟦axs_outputs⟧
120→
121→The outputs of depot initialization are:
122→
123→- Validated {rbra_rubric_repo_url} — confirmed reachable via `git ls-remote`
124→- Active {rbtgi_source_connection} — `installationState.stage` is `COMPLETE`
125→- OAuth token automatically stored in Secret Manager (managed by Developer Connect, not by operator)
126→
127→// ⟦axs_completion⟧
128→
129→Successful execution confirms the depot is fully initialized for
130→{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
131→operations.
132→The
133→{rbra_rubric_repo_url}
134→enables {rbtgr_rubric_repo} management and the
135→{rbtgi_source_connection}
136→enables Cloud Build to access the {rbtgr_rubric_repo}.
137→Proceed to
138→{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
139→to set up per-vessel build infrastructure.
140→

